    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for political entities considered of the highest order or level in a political hierarchical arrangement, but where the entity is historical and no longer exists. Examples are former nations, states, or empires, such as the Byzantine Empire.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
